                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d613">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.51/525: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-12-18T16:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 18, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>67. Your 155, December 6, 3 p.m. As you were informed through the Department’s
                    instructions 467, 468 and 470,<note n="18" xml:id="d613fn18">None
                        printed.</note> the competent agencies <pb facs="0549" n="543"
                        xml:id="pg_543"/> of this Government, after carefully considering the
                    Iranian Chargé’s inquiries last September as to possibility of obtaining a
                    $15,000,000 loan, did not find it in their competence to make such a loan; nor
                    have they the available funds. The Iranian Government, of course, enjoys free
                    access to unofficial sources of credit in this country but the attitude of the
                    latter depends on their own judgment of financial conditions. The Department is
                    informing the appropriate agencies of this Government of the contents of your
                    telegram under acknowledgment for their further consideration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
